values:
not that anyone cares.... here we go! 5 in one entry? why not!

Day 06 – Your day, in great detail

I woke up at around seven thirty- brushed my teeth, had a shower, ate yogurt/granola, watched veronica mars. Left my house at 8:40 and walked to work... got there about ten minutes early so I read a magazine until 9:30... then I worked. I did some organizing, a colour order, booked some appointments... dusted... very exciting. My manager's getting married in a few weeks and will be away from the salon for two weeks. For whatever reason, it's been decided that I am her stand-in... so we talked about that... and I get to go to the Aveda holiday launch party with my boss... so that's exciting because I get to dress up and then have an awkward evening of mingling with salon owners at a very nice restaurant. I have never been to a work event that wasn't just my coworkers, so I am intrigued. Anyway, so I worked untill 5:30 and then I walked home... and when I walk home I walk through a pretty sketchy area, which is also the only area where people in this city find me a suitable dating partner. Met a guy who just moved here from Toronto and says it's not very fun because there is no marineworld or wonderland? I asked him if that's what he did all the time in Toronto and he said yes. And then he insulted the Calgary Tower. Needless to say, very incompatible. Not to mention the fact that he is likely a drug dealer???? Hate to generalize. Anyway the rest of my walk was uneventful, drank an iced coffee and listened to cbc radio 3 the breakfast club podcast. I've now been home for about a half hour... tonight I will probably go to a techno show and watch people dance like lunatics. 

Day 07 – Your best friend, in great detail

Well I'm a grownup so I don't say best friend anymore. But I guess the friend I am around most is Marcella and she is slightly taller than me with dark brown hair and brown eyes. She's pretty fun I guess. I don't know what to say!!! She loves techno music and 80s metal... and wearing shirts off of her shoulder. Because of her, I feel as though my life resembles the eighties more than any other decade. 

Day 08 – A moment, in great detail

Oh my god!!! What moment? Got new glasses and man they are headache inducing... i feel as though i'm wobbling everywhere in them. that's a moment i guess. glasses shopping is the worst- nothing looks good.... too wide, too narrow, too big at the nose, curve up at the side, ugly handles, etc etc etc. then you get paranoid and realize that not even the glasses you've been wearing every day for two years look good!!! what are you supposed to do?

Day 09 – Your beliefs, in great detail

i believe that if every person could feel healthy, be happy, and feel whole that there would be no fights. i also believe that some of these goals can be achieved differently depending on the individual. this is the great benefit of religion- helps people feel whole. i'm not religious and i have a hard time, but also can't get behind most religions for myself. something is going on on planet earth and i'm not loving it. i wish that instead of fighting wars, designing new novelty food products (even though i love them) and focusing on what is wrong with ourselves (and this is what most of my brain energy is dedicated to) that we could focus on lifting everyone up. change the way food is viewed/sold/made, love ourselves, have patience, understanding and gratitude and feel balanced... instead people focus on tearing others down.

basically these beliefs are the things that will change/improve my life, and i think the root of many common problems today. ahhhh utopia!!!

Day 10 – What you wore today, in great detail
I am wearing an ill-fitting nude bra, a blue tri-blend american apparel v-neck, red bikini underwear, black levis, black toms, and my glasses. when i was outside i was also wearing a navy blue american apparel hoodie and a red flannel jacket. it is a boring outfit, but also super flattering, as my least favourite coworker told me i look as though i am withering away. trust, she meant it as a compliment.

Day 05 – Your definition of love, in great detail

love seems to be this magical healing tool that will fix your life because every night someone is cuddling you and there is someone that legitimately cares about how your day was and wants you to be happy, and in return you want to do everything for them. while there are people that i'd like to do everything for, i think love is a lot less exciting idea like that? life never is as exciting or beautiful or smooth as a movie and love stresses people out, they fight, they get annoyed with eachother, feelings are hidden, etc. i hear there are good parts but i don't often see them. that said- i love people who do whatever they want and show me their flaws, and i love happy people, people who laugh and who make me laugh, and i love people wearing good outfits or people with admirable dance skills... so i am free with my love, but not with my trust, and i feel that what i consider trust, others may consider love? i feel like i'm going to grow old loving everything, but not anyone. seems like people only become people that you say 'i love you' to if you trust them, so it's possibly something i'll miss out on unless i make a serious life change.

i try not to look at that as a bad thing, anyway. at least i enjoy my life and think the world is an interesting, cool, weird and magical place? idk it holds me over

okay i'm gonna do this, and i started on the second, doing day one and two because then i thought i would be all caught up. however, i've been raving too hard and saved it without posting it, so now this entry shall include the first four days i guess. 

Day 01 – Introduce yourself

my name is karen zurek, i live in calgary, alberta, canada. i have red hair that is approximately chin length, blue eyes and big old glasses. i work at a hair salon as a "promotions coordinator" which means i coordinate everyone's life for them and make posters in adobe illustrator. and also send e-mail newsletters and talk to funny people all day. i live with my friend named marcella, she's pretty funny. most of my life is spent sitting and laughing and eating. my memoir will be called eat, sit, laugh and nobody will read it. i am lucky enough to have other great people in my life, too. maybe i'll get a chance to talk about them later this month. sometimes i am happy and sometimes i am sad, but i have a pretty great life overall. i like to read, i like listening to music, i like making things, i like to walk and to sleep in clean sheets. i do a little of each every day to keep everything balanced.

Day 02 – Your first love, in great detail

well i have never been in love with a person, so i don't have a first one to talk about, but i love all sorts of things so i'll talk about them a bit. i love summer and waking up early on saturday mornings to get coffee and shop for used books. i love going to bed early, and i love staying up all night because i am excited about something. i love bouncing around, i love learning things, i love music, i love ideas! i guess what i'm saying here is that i love my life and every time i'm in a really great space i look around in awe and think "i love my life for the very first time!!!" so maybe my first love is me, and how awesome i am!!! 

sorry, i'm working on my self confidence. but i do think that loving yourself is a huge key to loving other people, because normally i disgust myself and so does everyone else. but when i love myself? i love, or at least tolerate, everyone else!

Day 03 – Your parents, in great detail

my dad is a quiet, miserable seeming kind of guy, but he rules. he is 52 and lives with my mom and sisters. he has a job that he thinks is just okay. he has been all over the world and is a pretty good storyteller. he has gray hair and blue eyes, wears untrendy dad clothes and is always fixing things. traits we share: introverted,  curious, excitable, awkward in social situations.

my mom is just crazy. she has back problems so she doesn't work, so most of the time she watches the food network, reads about food/internet memes online, rides her cooler scooter around, and hangs out in a hut she made my dad build in the backyard for her. this is called 'the shack' and all of her friends come over and drink in it. it legitimately looks straight out of a ridiculous sitcom, i can't believe it's in my life. that said, i love my mom. she's always trying to feed me, she sometimes does nice things, and she has found a way to enjoy her life. we both stress out about ridiculous things, get huffy instead of verbally upset, and fall asleep in movies all the time. 

Day 04 – What you ate today, in great detail

well, all i've consumed today is water and a mocha. the water was in a ship regulars cup, and unfortunately was not enjoyable because it had been sitting beside my bed all night, but i was thirsty. the mocha i got at the purple perk, because i've developed an obsession with coffee shops and am trying them all. however, not reaaally diggin my coffee and don't know if it's going to be where i go to hang out. i decided i need somewhere to hang out in the winter that's not my house, work, or a bar, and a coffee shop seems like a safe, obvious, and nice idea.

i am feeling better about life on a daily basis. i mean, here i am! twenty years old, laying on my stomach with a wealth of knowledge at my fingertips and a delightful slushy beverage. i'm finding it more difficult, if only slightly, to see the bad in situations. life is weird, people are slipping away on a daily basis. new people are sprouting with springtime and it's just the circle of life. or something. god almighty!

yesterday i finally finished atlas shrugged, which marks the longest time i have ever spent reading a book in my entire life. and then today, i read anthem in its entirety. i've got my fill of ayn rand for a bit. tomorrow morning i will start brave new world. after that i think i'm just gonna read some zadie smith or something. i need a break from srs business.

i still love my job which is highly unusual for myself. today i retaught myself how to make formulas in microsoft excel which is a nice accomplishment i think. other than that, life is boring. i have launched a search for a boy best friend and i think i should see premium results soon. i hate the new facebook chat, not that i loved it before. my feet are cold, i can't find my needle, etc etcetc

"For I have known them all already, known them all:—
Have known the evenings, mornings, afternoons,
I have measured out my life with coffee spoons;
I know the voices dying with a dying fall
Beneath the music from a farther room.
 

So how should I presume?"



I wish I knew what to write in here but everything is too personal or too crass. Life is okay. People need to focus on the positive, minimize the negative and not invent things that don't need to be invented. Youuu know.

-it to be warmer than 1 degree tomorrow
-someone to wash and blowdry my hair right now
-clean laundryyyy
-a million dollars
-a job number two
-to not be sooo full right now
-a fridge full of groceries (especially watermelon)
-every band i like to come here
-more more more
I came from nothing and I will end as nothing, but in between I would like to be something.

Life changes on a daily basis, so today I am just appreciating the light that comes through my blinds, the people that i care about/who care about me, water, clean hair and that soon it will be summer. I'm on a search for something but I couldn't even tell you what it is, something is just missing. I want to know everything about everyone, and I want to see a video of how happy I was as a fifteen year old because today I've been reading my internet past and I just don't remember being so giddy. And I want a hug because I have had a rough few weeks.

No more, though.

I'm sure no one will find this interesting but I took pictures of me doing my homework for some reason and now I'm bored enough to post them. So, here is my life basically. I start with the body. This assignment was a paper doll collection based on the late 1940s, early 1950s. When I do normal homework, I don't usually draw underwear on them. Now I draw the clothes in pencil on normal printer paper. When I've decided they are acceptable, I trace them onto marker paper and then outline them with a black micron pen. Using prismacolour markers, I colour the outfits, adding highlights and shadows. Then, I use white and black pencil crayons to further add highlights and shadows. I also had to draw accessories. They were done exactly the same way as the clothing. I then cut the items out and glued them onto white cardstock. To add to the paperdoll effect, I drew dotted black lines and little tabs with a black micron pen. Then, I glued them to more cardstock. In the upper right corner I wrote the dolls name (Ava) and the activity she would wear the outfit to. Sorting out outfits. Gluing. The doll and her crinoline. Ava entertains. Ava goes to lunch. I really messed up the stripes on this one. Ava goes out on the town. Ava goes to church. Ava goes to school. It wasn't a huge assignment but it took me what felt like forever. In other news, there is some sort of bird pecking at my wall incessantly and I am incredibly bored. Also I have an incredibly runny nose. Ohh life. Well, I'm done school! Minus exams, but whooo cares?
